Use this README file to introduce your application and point to useful places in the API for learning more.
Run "rake doc:app" to generate API documentation for your models, controllers, helpers, and libraries.

Installation steps

You will need to install Ruby 1.9.3 or higher for compatibility with the latest version of rails. On Ubuntu this can be done by using the installRuby193.sh shell script in this directory.

You will need to have sqlite3 and dev libraries: sudo aptitude install libsqlite3-dev sqlite3
You also need a javascript runtime. The easiest way to get this is to install node.js using the instructions on: http://github.com/joyent/node/wiki/installing-Node.js-via-package-manager 
Once you have Ruby you need to get rails with: sudo gem install rails
Once all this is done you can use bundle to install everything else: sudo bundle install
Now you need the database: rake db:migrate
Finally apply the patch at https://bugs.ruby-lang.org/attachments/2300/204_304_keep_alive.patch to the code in the directory located by gem which webrick


